00:12:16,669 --> 00:12:19,372
-Is it good?
-It's the best.

254
00:12:19,439 --> 00:12:23,543
This is so well-seasoned
and the texture is incredible.

255
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:24,911
It's amazing.

256
00:12:25,311 --> 00:12:27,046
The sweetness of
the veggies is irresistible.

257
00:12:27,113 --> 00:12:29,215
I agree. The sweetness of the vegetables…

258
00:12:29,849 --> 00:12:33,586
-And that sound is so nice, too.
-Isn’t it?

259
00:12:33,653 --> 00:12:36,856
It lets you know that
someone is making it with care.

260
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:41,594
Should we have okonomiyaki and yakisoba?

261
00:12:41,661 --> 00:12:42,929
Sure. Yakisoba.

262
00:12:43,563 --> 00:12:45,665
-Is okonomiyaki with everything the best?
-Right.

263
00:12:45,732 --> 00:12:46,633
-With everything.
-Yes.

264
00:12:46,733 --> 00:12:49,068
And for yakisoba…

265
00:12:50,103 --> 00:12:51,504
Are there that many kinds?

266
00:12:51,571 --> 00:12:53,706
I'm trying to decide
what toppings to put in it.

267
00:12:53,773 --> 00:12:56,876
A lot of customers order
the one with everything.

268
00:12:56,943 --> 00:12:59,679
-It comes with a fried egg on top.
-Then we'll go with that!

269
00:12:59,746 --> 00:13:00,980
-Sounds good.
-Okay.

270
00:13:01,047 --> 00:13:03,182
What's the difference between

271
00:13:03,249 --> 00:13:06,219
Hiroshima-style
and Osaka-style okonomiyaki?

272
00:13:06,286 --> 00:13:08,154
Koreans don't really know.

273
00:13:08,221 --> 00:13:09,522
Really?

274
00:13:09,589 --> 00:13:12,692
-They look pretty similar.
-Well, that's…

275
00:13:12,759 --> 00:13:14,827
If you say, "They’re all the same,"

276
00:13:14,894 --> 00:13:17,764
Osaka people get mad,

277
00:13:17,830 --> 00:13:19,632
and Hiroshima people say,
"They’re different!"

278
00:13:21,463 --> 00:13:24,070
OSAKA-STYLE VS HIROSHIMA-STYLE

279
00:13:24,837 --> 00:13:28,841
THE NEVER-ENDING DEBATE

280
00:13:28,908 --> 00:13:32,345
We use more batter in Osaka.

281
00:13:32,945 --> 00:13:34,347
OSAKA-STYLE

282
00:13:34,414 --> 00:13:37,150
EVERYTHING IS MIXED
INTO THE BATTER AND GRILLED

283
00:13:37,216 --> 00:13:40,720
In Hiroshima, they stack the cabbage
and steam it on the griddle.

284
00:13:41,016 --> 00:13:42,159
HIROSHIMA-STYLE

285
00:13:42,334 --> 00:13:44,657
GRILLED IN LAYERS, STEAMED FROM WITHIN

286
00:13:48,094 --> 00:13:52,732
MAIN DISH
OKONOMIYAKI

287
00:14:04,777 --> 00:14:06,546
He keeps his gaze on the food.

288
00:14:07,547 --> 00:14:08,848
He's cooking with care.

289
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:12,719
-He's in tune with the food.
-That's impressive.

290
00:14:13,453 --> 00:14:15,254
I just stand here and zone out.

291
00:14:15,321 --> 00:14:17,256
You're like, "I will make this delicious!"

292
00:14:18,224 --> 00:14:21,227
Even when it's busy,
you just stand there, focused.

293
00:14:21,294 --> 00:14:22,428
That is true.

294
00:14:22,495 --> 00:14:25,531
-When you work on several dishes at once…
-Yes.

295
00:14:25,598 --> 00:14:28,167
-…they cook at different times.
-Right.

296
00:14:28,234 --> 00:14:30,236
How do you know which one's done?
Just by instinct?

297
00:14:30,303 --> 00:14:31,504
I just know.

298
00:14:32,638 --> 00:14:34,407
That's like his stage.

299
00:14:40,922 --> 00:14:42,790
-Here.
-Okay.

300
00:14:44,450 --> 00:14:45,885
-Excuse me.
-It's here.

301
00:14:45,952 --> 00:14:47,520
Okonomiyaki with everything.

302
00:14:47,587 --> 00:14:49,055
Finally!

303
00:14:49,784 --> 00:14:53,526
OKONOMIYAKI WITH EVERYTHING
6,800 WON, 680 YEN

304
00:14:53,593 --> 00:14:55,294
-There's green laver powder…
-Okay

305
00:14:55,361 --> 00:14:57,063
…and bonito powder.

306
00:14:57,130 --> 00:14:58,131
-Good.
-Add to your taste.

307
00:14:58,197 --> 00:14:59,832
-All right.
-Okay.

308
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:01,701
I'll sprinkle a little.

309
00:15:02,301 --> 00:15:03,870
It's bonito powder.

310
00:15:08,408 --> 00:15:09,842
He knows what he's doing.

311
00:15:11,043 --> 00:15:12,879
Isn't that too much?

312
00:15:12,979 --> 00:15:14,247
Not at all.

313
00:15:14,313 --> 00:15:16,082
-Is this okay?
-Yes.

314
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:18,618
You can add as much as you want.

315
00:15:19,152 --> 00:15:22,221
-Let me use this for a second.
-Sure.

316
00:15:22,288 --> 00:15:25,691
And then you add
mayonnaise to your taste.

317
00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:26,826
Exactly.

318
00:15:35,368 --> 00:15:37,470
You're like an okonomiyaki warrior.

319
00:15:38,371 --> 00:15:39,906
-There. Let's dig in!
-Okay.

320
00:15:39,972 --> 00:15:41,808
I'm going to go wild…

321
00:15:44,043 --> 00:15:44,911
with mayo.

322
00:15:45,607 --> 00:15:47,847
MATJJIGAE'S STYLE
PILING ON THE MAYO

323
00:15:49,048 --> 00:15:51,417
SI-KYUNG'S STYLE
ADD MAYO

324
00:15:51,484 --> 00:15:55,788
AND SAUCE

325
00:15:56,389 --> 00:15:58,391
-I'll start.
-Enjoy.

326
00:16:05,131 --> 00:16:06,332
It's delicious.

327
00:16:13,139 --> 00:16:14,907
-It's good.
-Isn't it?

328
00:16:16,476 --> 00:16:18,211
It's light.

329
00:16:18,277 --> 00:16:20,480
-It just melts in your mouth.
-Right.

330
00:16:20,546 --> 00:16:24,050
You only notice the cabbage by its flavor.

331
00:16:24,116 --> 00:16:26,252
I can taste it, but I can't feel it.

332
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:28,221
-Very airy, right?
-Yes.

333
00:16:32,859 --> 00:16:35,061
You know, okonomiyaki
is usually on the heavier side.

334
00:16:35,127 --> 00:16:37,463
It can be quite dense with batter.

335
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:40,433
But with this one, the cabbage
just kind of melts away,

336
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:42,101
so you could eat a lot more.

337
00:16:42,168 --> 00:16:43,469
I can keep going.

338
00:16:43,536 --> 00:16:45,204
-I told you.
-Yes.

339
00:16:45,271 --> 00:16:47,473
It just keeps going in.

340
00:16:47,540 --> 00:16:49,876
I've never had anything like this.

341
00:16:49,942 --> 00:16:51,878
It changes your idea
of okonomiyaki, doesn't it?

342
00:16:51,944 --> 00:16:53,880
This is beyond fluffy.

343
00:16:55,515 --> 00:16:58,484
He really knows
how to add air to the batter.

344
00:16:58,551 --> 00:17:00,553
It puffed up beautifully.

345
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:01,521
This is amazing.

346
00:17:02,421 --> 00:17:05,358
It's got volume, but when you chew it…

347
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:07,793
It's airy.

348
00:17:07,860 --> 00:17:09,495
Right. Airy.

349
00:17:09,562 --> 00:17:12,965
This place is incredible. Really.

350
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:17,036
If you think anyone can make this dish,
you're seriously mistaken.

351
00:17:17,103 --> 00:17:18,871
-I agree.
-The way…

352
00:17:18,938 --> 00:17:22,074
he adds air is something else.

353
00:17:22,141 --> 00:17:23,743
Adding air is everything, right?

354
00:17:23,809 --> 00:17:25,545
-When you mix it.
-When we mix it?

355
00:17:25,611 --> 00:17:28,180
There's no special technique, though.

356
00:17:28,247 --> 00:17:30,583
There isn't?

357
00:17:30,650 --> 00:17:33,286
That was humblebragging.

358
00:17:33,352 --> 00:17:36,255
I think this is the best okonomiyaki

359
00:17:36,322 --> 00:17:38,124
I've had in Osaka.

360
00:17:38,190 --> 00:17:39,525
No doubt about it.

361
00:17:39,592 --> 00:17:42,495
I think it's the best in Japan.

362
00:17:42,562 --> 00:17:45,932
-This place is on another level.
-It really is.

363
00:17:45,998 --> 00:17:47,633
It's in a different league.

364
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:51,704
I never thought
I'd want to bring my parents

365
00:17:51,771 --> 00:17:54,574
to a place with sauce-covered okonomiyaki.

366
00:17:55,408 --> 00:17:56,709
It's usually heavy.

367
00:17:56,776 --> 00:18:01,514
But here, I'd love to come back
with my parents or seniors.

368
00:18:01,581 --> 00:18:03,749
They'd definitely say,

369
00:18:03,816 --> 00:18:05,618
-"This is amazing."
-Right.

370
00:18:05,685 --> 00:18:07,219
They'd definitely love it.

371
00:18:07,553 --> 00:18:09,822
I hope Koreans get to try this too.

372
00:18:09,889 --> 00:18:15,428
This might be the first time I've had
such a light, airy okonomiyaki.

373
00:18:15,494 --> 00:18:18,864
If you think this is
what okonomiyaki is supposed to be,

374
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:20,600
you won't be satisfied anywhere else.

375
00:18:20,666 --> 00:18:25,204
And you didn't find this place online.

376
00:18:25,271 --> 00:18:26,706
You just stumbled upon it.

377
00:18:26,772 --> 00:18:30,943
Basically, some higher power led me here.

378
00:18:31,010 --> 00:18:35,068
I heard cabbage prices in Japan
skyrocketed. It must've been tough.

379
00:18:35,147 --> 00:18:37,583
It must have been tough
when cabbage prices went up.

380
00:18:37,650 --> 00:18:39,385
Yes, it was rough.

381
00:18:39,452 --> 00:18:42,021
But we had to buy it anyway.

382
00:18:42,088 --> 00:18:43,623
We can't run the business without it.

383
00:18:43,689 --> 00:18:44,624
True.

384
00:18:44,690 --> 00:18:48,427
If napa cabbage prices go up in Korea,

385
00:18:48,494 --> 00:18:49,929
-restaurants really struggle.
-I bet.

386
00:18:49,996 --> 00:18:52,665
-Because kimchi is free.
-Right.

387
00:18:52,732 --> 00:18:54,333
-For restaurants in Japan…
-So it's tough.

388
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:56,702
…the only thing you get for free

389
00:18:56,802 --> 00:18:59,138
is water that they give you
at the beginning.

390
00:18:59,205 --> 00:19:01,040
Even otoshi,
a small appetizer, isn't free.

391
00:19:01,107 --> 00:19:03,442
Do you have otoshi in Korea?

392
00:19:03,709 --> 00:19:04,944
-No.
-Really?

393
00:19:05,011 --> 00:19:08,648
-Yes.
-Maybe someone should speak up and say,

394
00:19:08,714 --> 00:19:11,584
"Let's stop giving out free kimchi."

395
00:19:11,651 --> 00:19:14,320
If I ever said that,
I'd probably have to retire.

396
00:19:14,387 --> 00:19:15,655
You'd be done for.

397
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:21,027
If you're okay with that,
maybe you should say it.

398
00:19:21,093 --> 00:19:24,997
Think of the people who make kimchi.

399
00:19:25,064 --> 00:19:29,835
We should start a campaign.
"Time to charge for kimchi!"

400
00:19:29,902 --> 00:19:33,172
Making kimchi takes so much work.

401
00:19:33,239 --> 00:19:37,043
So most restaurants have given up
making it themselves

402
00:19:37,109 --> 00:19:40,246
-and just import it, which is sad.
-That's…

403
00:19:40,312 --> 00:19:42,815
-just bad for everyone.
-I agree.

404
00:19:42,882 --> 00:19:46,686
People would want real Korean kimchi,
even if they had to pay.

405
00:19:46,752 --> 00:19:48,888
It might be better to charge customers

406
00:19:48,954 --> 00:19:51,691
for properly-made Korean kimchi.

407
00:19:54,794 --> 00:19:57,930
Here's your yakisoba.

408
00:19:59,465 --> 00:20:00,733
This sound.

409
00:20:01,429 --> 00:20:05,004
YAKISOBA WITH EVERYTHING
7,300 WON, 730 YEN

410
00:20:05,071 --> 00:20:09,162
MAIN DISH
YAKISOBA

411
00:20:18,284 --> 00:20:21,520
Jjajangmyeon led us to this.

412
00:20:21,587 --> 00:20:23,556
-This is what we came for.
-Right.

413
00:20:24,123 --> 00:20:27,059
-I don't know if it's okay to say this…
-Yes?

414
00:20:27,126 --> 00:20:31,263
But it’s like eating
the most basic yakisoba

415
00:20:31,330 --> 00:20:33,099
without any vegetables.

416
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:35,668
Yakisoba has a nostalgic taste,
and jjajangmyeon is the same.

417
00:20:42,975 --> 00:20:44,944
-This is the real deal.
-Do we eat it as is?

418
00:20:45,010 --> 00:20:48,514
You can sprinkle
green laver powder if you want.

419
00:20:58,190 --> 00:20:59,458
How is it?

420
00:20:59,525 --> 00:21:01,360
Delicious.

421
00:21:01,894 --> 00:21:03,863
They're all sauce-based dishes

422
00:21:03,929 --> 00:21:05,865
but they all taste different.

423
00:21:06,499 --> 00:21:09,401
In some places, you can't even tell
what you ate.

424
00:21:09,468 --> 00:21:10,936
Their dishes taste the same.

425
00:21:18,611 --> 00:21:19,612
What do you think?

426
00:21:20,679 --> 00:21:24,150
I could eat three servings of this
all by myself.

427
00:21:24,216 --> 00:21:25,184
Right?

428
00:21:25,251 --> 00:21:28,187
Everyone who comes here

429
00:21:28,254 --> 00:21:31,223
gulps down the food
as if they're going to order

430
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:32,691
the entire menu.

431
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:34,226
This is the best.

432
00:21:37,196 --> 00:21:38,764
It tastes kind of like jjajangmyeon too.

433
00:21:38,831 --> 00:21:40,132
-Doesn't it?
-Yes.

434
00:21:41,066 --> 00:21:46,105
Even Japanese people who've eaten
yakisoba and okonomiyaki to death

435
00:21:46,172 --> 00:21:47,606
-would be blown away.
-Totally.

436
00:21:47,673 --> 00:21:49,108
-Right?
-I was really shocked.

437
00:21:49,175 --> 00:21:50,042
It's so good.

438
00:21:51,977 --> 00:21:53,345
This is so delicious.

439
00:21:55,881 --> 00:21:57,116
Thank you.

440
00:21:57,183 --> 00:21:59,185
Deep down,

441
00:21:59,251 --> 00:22:01,687
I wanted to keep this place to myself.

442
00:22:01,754 --> 00:22:03,022
I'm sorry.

443
00:22:03,656 --> 00:22:05,324
There's no going back now.

444
00:22:05,391 --> 00:22:07,293
I really didn't want to tell anyone.

445
00:22:23,142 --> 00:22:24,310
This is dangerous.

446
00:22:27,279 --> 00:22:29,515
I just can't stop eating.

447
00:22:29,582 --> 00:22:30,783
What should I do?

448
00:22:30,850 --> 00:22:32,251
You should come here again.

449
00:22:32,318 --> 00:22:35,521
You'll have to come back soon.

450
00:22:35,588 --> 00:22:37,022
I should stop eating.

451
00:22:38,858 --> 00:22:41,627
I genuinely want to come here again.

452
00:22:41,694 --> 00:22:43,028
Nice.

453
00:22:43,095 --> 00:22:44,830
What time do you open?

454
00:22:44,897 --> 00:22:46,365
We open at 11:30 a.m.

455
00:22:47,628 --> 00:22:49,168
When do we leave,
the day after tomorrow?

